Dear Nkwenti,

We have received complaints about your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup), specifically about the following IP address(es):

213.199.52.155

Please see the forwarded e-mail below for more details. Apparently, your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup) is used for phishing which is strictly forbidden by our ToS.

Abuse is a serious threat in the Internet and can cause a huge amount of damage; thus, we ask for your understanding that once an ABUSE case is reported to us, we must handle abuse strictly and with no tolerance.

Please take immediate action to stop the ongoing server misuse. It is required that you solve the problem within the next 12 hours, and that we receive your reply within this period, too. Your reply must contain all information which enable us to understand exactly which measures you took to stop the abuse and prevent such or similar incidents in the future.

We will suspend access to your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup) if we do not receive your reply within the given time frame, and if the problem is not solved in due time; both is essential - the solution and your response. The reactivation of a VPS 4 NVMe (no setup) always demands a reactivation fee of at least $46.00. Please respond in due time to save these expenses.

We would appreciate your immediate attention to this matter.

The attached guide for troubleshooting includes some useful information.

Issue 71399923: Malicious web shell at hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php

> Sehr geehrte Damen und Herren!
> 
> Wir haben eine schädliche Web-Shell entdeckt, welche in Ihrem Netzwerk gehostet wird:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php [213.199.52.155]
> 
> Web-Shells sind Skripte, welche Angreifer auf kompromittierte Webserver hochladen, um Fernzugriff zu erhalten. Beim Zugriff über einen Webbrowser können Angreifer mithilfe von Web-Shells Dateien hochladen, beliebige Befehle auf dem Server ausführen und Spam senden. Web-Shells werden häufig verwendet, um Phishing- oder Malware-Angriffe auf dem kompromittierten Server zu erstellen.
> 
> Angreifer versuchen oft, Web-Shells als harmlose Seiten zu tarnen. Zu den gängigen Techniken gehört das Zurückgeben einer gefälschten 404-Seite und das Unsichtbarmachen der Web-Shell-Eingabefelder auf der Seite. Überprüfen Sie, ob der Angreifer nicht versucht, die Web-Shell auszublenden, bevor Sie diesen Bericht schließen.
> 
> Weitere Informationen zum erkannten Problem finden Sie unter https://incident.netcraft.com/659283988493/
>

> Dear Sir or Madam,
> 
> We have discovered a malicious web shell being hosted on your network:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php [213.199.52.155]
> 
> Web shells are scripts that attackers upload to compromised web-servers in order to gain remote access. When accessed using a web browser, web shells can allow attackers to upload files, execute arbitrary commands on the server, and send spam. Web shells are often used to create phishing or malware attacks on the compromised server.
> 
> Attackers often attempt to disguise web shells as benign pages. Common techniques include returning a fake 404 page and making the web shell input fields on the page invisible. Please check the attacker is not attempting to hide the web shell before dismissing this report.
> 
> More information about the detected issue is provided at https://incident.netcraft.com/659283988493/
> 
> NEW: A beta version of our next generation incident reports is available at https://beta.incident.netcraft.com/reports/as2272h33py6wvkzm3yeth
> See https://beta.incident.netcraft.com/about for more details including API support. Please contact incident-feedback@netcraft.com with any feedback or for more information.
> 
> Regards,
> 
> Netcraft
> 
> Phone: +44(0)1225 447500

Body:
Dear Nkwenti,

Unfortunately, we have not received a reply from you regarding the resolution of the complaint which we recently forwarded to you by email.

To prevent further misuse of your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup), we had to temporarily suspend server access.

It is our most important goal to work together with you and find a solution to the issue. That's why we ask you to get in touch with us immediately. Please note that the temporary suspension does not affect the contract; the contract will keep on renewing without your adequate reaction. To cover our efforts involved in handling this complaint, we will charge a reactivation fee of $46.00. Upon receipt of your payment, we can reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup) and you can take the necessary steps to stop the abuse.

Please go to https://my.contabo.com/account/payment_method/?utm_medium=email and pay the reactivation fee of $46.00 using an immediate payment method like PayPal. 

Please respond to this email as soon as your payment is available on your customer account. Without your response we cannot reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (no setup), even if you have sent the payment.

Also, please note that emails can arrive in the spam folder of an email account. Should you miss the complaint which we have sent to you, please check your spam folder carefully to be on the safe side. Morover, please add abuse@contabo.com to the list of trustworthy contacts in your mail client / on your mail server, so you'll get all our emails in your regular inbox in the future.

06/19/2025 15:22 (Europe/Berlin) - Netcraft Takedown Service wrote:

> 
> Sehr geehrte Damen und Herren!
> 
> Wir haben eine schädliche Web-Shell entdeckt, welche in Ihrem Netzwerk
> gehostet
> wird:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php [213.199.52.155]
> 
> Web-Shells sind Skripte, welche Angreifer auf kompromittierte Webserver
> hochladen,
> um Fernzugriff zu erhalten. Beim Zugriff über einen Webbrowser können
> Angreifer
> mithilfe von Web-Shells Dateien hochladen, beliebige Befehle auf dem Server
> ausführen und Spam senden. Web-Shells werden häufig verwendet, um Phishing-
> oder
> Malware-Angriffe auf dem kompromittierten Server zu erstellen.
> 
> Angreifer versuchen oft, Web-Shells als harmlose Seiten zu tarnen. Zu den
> gängigen
> Techniken gehört das Zurückgeben einer gefälschten 404-Seite und das
> Unsichtbarmachen der Web-Shell-Eingabefelder auf der Seite. Überprüfen Sie, ob
> der
> Angreifer nicht versucht, die Web-Shell auszublenden, bevor Sie diesen Bericht
> schließen.
> 
> Wir haben Sie zuvor wegen dieses Problems unter 2025-06-19 12:25:25 (UTC)
> kontaktiert.
> Seit unserer letzten Benachrichtigung wurden die folgenden zusätzlichen URL(s)
> erkannt:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.php
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.php
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.php
> 
> Weitere Informationen zum erkannten Problem finden Sie unter
> [2]https://incident.netcraft.com/659283988493/
> 
> NEU: Eine Betaversion unserer Vorfallberichte der nächsten Generation ist
> unter
> [3]https://beta.incident.netcraft.com/reports/as2272h33py6wvkzm3yeth
> verfügbar.
> Weitere Details, einschließlich API-Unterstützung, finden Sie unter
> [4]https://beta.incident.netcraft.com/about. Bitte wenden Sie sich für
> Feedback oder
> weitere Informationen an incident-feedback@netcraft.com
> 
> Mit besten Grüßen,
> 
> Netcraft
>

> -------------------
> Dear Sir or Madam,
> 
> We have discovered a malicious web shell being hosted on your network:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php [213.199.52.155]
> 
> Web shells are scripts that attackers upload to compromised web-servers in
> order
> to gain remote access. When accessed using a web browser, web shells can allow
> attackers to upload files, execute arbitrary commands on the server, and send
> spam. Web shells are often used to create phishing or malware attacks on the
> compromised server.
> 
> Attackers often attempt to disguise web shells as benign pages. Common
> techniques
> include returning a fake 404 page and making the web shell input fields on the
> page invisible. Please check the attacker is not attempting to hide the web
> shell
> before dismissing this report.
> 
> We previously contacted you about this issue on 2025-06-19 12:25:25 (UTC).
> Since our last notification, the following additional URL(s) have been
> detected:
> 
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.php
> hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.php

Beim Zugriff über einen Webbrowser können Angreifermithilfe von Web-Shells Dateien hochladen, beliebige Befehle auf dem Serverausführen und Spam senden. Web-Shells werden häufig verwendet, um Phishing- oderMalware-Angriffe auf dem kompromittierten Server zu erstellen.Angreifer versuchen oft, Web-Shells als harmlose Seiten zu tarnen. Zu den gängigenTechniken gehört das Zurückgeben einer gefälschten 404-Seite und dasUnsichtbarmachen der Web-Shell-Eingabefelder auf der Seite. Überprüfen Sie, ob derAngreifer nicht versucht, die Web-Shell auszublenden, bevor Sie diesen Berichtschließen.Wir haben Sie zuvor wegen dieses Problems unter 2025-06-19 12:25:25 (UTC)kontaktiert.Seit unserer letzten Benachrichtigung wurden die folgenden zusätzlichen URL(s)erkannt:hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.phphxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.phphxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.phpWeitere Informationen zum erkannten Problem finden Sie unterhttps://incident.netcraft.com/659283988493/NEU: Eine Betaversion unserer Vorfallberichte der nächsten Generation ist unterhttps://beta.incident.netcraft.com/reports/as2272h33py6wvkzm3yeth verfügbar.Weitere Details, einschließlich API-Unterstützung, finden Sie unterhttps://beta.incident.netcraft.com/about. Bitte wenden Sie sich für Feedback oderweitere Informationen an incident-feedback@netcraft.comMit besten Grüßen,NetcraftTelefon: +44(0)1225 447500Fax: +44(0)1225 448600Netcraft-Ausgabenummer: 71399923Um Aktualisierungen über diesen Angriff zu erhalten, antworten Sie bitte auf dieseE-Mail. Weitere Informationen überX-ARF-Tools finden Sie unter http://www.xarf.org/-------------------Dear Sir or Madam,We have discovered a malicious web shell being hosted on your network:hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.php [213.199.52.155]hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.php [213.199.52.155]hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.php [213.199.52.155]hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-includes/product.php [213.199.52.155]Web shells are scripts that attackers upload to compromised web-servers in orderto gain remote access. When accessed using a web browser, web shells can allowattackers to upload files, execute arbitrary commands on the server, and sendspam. Web shells are often used to create phishing or malware attacks on thecompromised server.Attackers often attempt to disguise web shells as benign pages. Common techniquesinclude returning a fake 404 page and making the web shell input fields on thepage invisible. Please check the attacker is not attempting to hide the web shellbefore dismissing this report.We previously contacted you about this issue on 2025-06-19 12:25:25 (UTC).Since our last notification, the following additional URL(s) have been detected:hxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-admin/wp-log1n.phphxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/click.phphxxp://caliheilblatt[.]com/wp-content/install.phpMore information about the detected issue is provided athttps://incident.netcraft.com/659283988493/NEW: A beta version of our next generation incident reports is available athttps://beta.incident.netcraft.com/reports/as2272h33py6wvkzm3yethSee https://beta.incident.netcraft.com/about for more details including APIsupport.  complaint
From: Contabo Trust & Compliance Team <abuse@contabo.com>
To: tangentohost@gmail.com
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 01:10:11 +0000
Priority: high
----------------------------------------
Body:
Dear Nkwenti,

Unfortunately, we have not received a reply from you regarding the resolution of the complaint which we recently forwarded to you by email.

To prevent further misuse of your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com), we had to temporarily suspend server access.

It is our most important goal to work together with you and find a solution to the issue. That's why we ask you to get in touch with us immediately. Please note that the temporary suspension does not affect the contract; the contract will keep on renewing without your adequate reaction. To cover our efforts involved in handling this complaint, we will charge a reactivation fee of $46.00. Upon receipt of your payment, we can reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com) and you can take the necessary steps to stop the abuse.

Please go to https://my.contabo.com/account/payment_method/?utm_medium=email and pay the reactivation fee of $46.00 using an immediate payment method like PayPal. 

Please respond to this email as soon as your payment is available on your customer account. Without your response we cannot reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com), even if you have sent the payment.

Also, please note that emails can arrive in the spam folder of an email account. Should you miss the complaint which we have sent to you, please check your spam folder carefully to be on the safe side. Morover, please add abuse@contabo.com to the list of trustworthy contacts in your mail client / on your mail server, so you'll get all our emails in your regular inbox in the future.

--
Best regards,

Dear Nkwenti,

We have received complaints about your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com), specifically about the following IP address(es):

213.199.52.155

Please see the forwarded e-mail below for more details. Apparently, your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com) is used for phishing which is strictly forbidden by our ToS.

Abuse is a serious threat in the Internet and can cause a huge amount of damage; thus, we ask for your understanding that once an ABUSE case is reported to us, we must handle abuse strictly and with no tolerance.

Please take immediate action to stop the ongoing server misuse. It is required that you solve the problem within the next 12 hours, and that we receive your reply within this period, too. Your reply must contain all information which enable us to understand exactly which measures you took to stop the abuse and prevent such or similar incidents in the future.

We will suspend access to your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com) if we do not receive your reply within the given time frame, and if the problem is not solved in due time; both is essential - the solution and your response. The reactivation of a VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com) always demands a reactivation fee of at least $46.00. Please respond in due time to save these expenses.

We would appreciate your immediate attention to this matter.

> hxxps://payunix[.]com/Agency404/pc/payment.php [213.199.52.155]
> hxxps://payunix[.]com/Agency404/pc/404notfound2.php [213.199.52.155]

> hxxps://payunix[.]com/Agency404/pc/otp.php [213.199.52.155]

> Website unseres Kunden ist auf [2]https://www.originenergy.com.au/ zu finden.

> Bitte löschen Sie diesen und jeden damit verbundenen betrügerischen Inhalt so
> bald
> wie möglich.

> bestimmten Ländern aus sichtbar ist. Bevor Sie entscheiden, dass der Angriff

> Australien

> kontaktiert.

Ticket ID: TMS20250802396528
Subject: [Ticket#2025080110005959] [Action required] Your VPS 4 NVMe
 (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com): Suspension due to abuse
 complaint
From: Contabo Trust & Compliance Team <abuse@contabo.com>
To: tangentohost@gmail.com
Date: Sat, 2 Aug 2025 04:50:07 +0000
Priority: high
----------------------------------------
Body:
Dear Nkwenti,

Unfortunately, we have not received a reply from you regarding the resolution of the complaint which we recently forwarded to you by email.

To prevent further misuse of your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com), we had to temporarily suspend server access.

It is our most important goal to work together with you and find a solution to the issue. That's why we ask you to get in touch with us immediately. Please note that the temporary suspension does not affect the contract; the contract will keep on renewing without your adequate reaction. To cover our efforts involved in handling this complaint, we will charge a reactivation fee of $46.00. Upon receipt of your payment, we can reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com) and you can take the necessary steps to stop the abuse.

Please go to https://my.contabo.com/account/payment_method/?utm_medium=email and pay the reactivation fee of $46.00 using an immediate payment method like PayPal. 

Please respond to this email as soon as your payment is available on your customer account. Without your response we cannot reactivate your VPS 4 NVMe (213.199.52.155 - server.tangentohost.com), even if you have sent the payment.

Also, please note that emails can arrive in the spam folder of an email account. Should you miss the complaint which we have sent to you, please check your spam folder carefully to be on the safe side.
